1)Advanced Rest Client

2)What is integration

client will call API before hitting API server will perform (Authentication(who are you) then authorization(what accesss you have )then response (success/fail))

3) Types of Authentication

  1) No authentication (not for salesforce)
  2) Basic authentication (user name and password)
        ex:freshdesk
  3) API-Key Based Authentication
        ex:OpnecageGeoCoder,exchangeRate
  4) OAuth 1.0 (deprecated) ex: twitter 
  5) OAuth 2.0
      1) Web-server flow
      2) User Agent flow
      3) UserName and password flow (Deprecated)
      4) Refresh Token flow
      5) JWT Bearer flow for server to server Integration
      6) client credential flow for server to server Integration
      7) Device Flow for IOT Device
      8) SAML Bearer assertion flow for previously authorized app (will not study)
      9) PKCE
4) Google chrome extension --->JSON Formatter

5) HTTPRequest -->prepare request
   http -->has send method that takes instance of HttpRequest and sends to thirdparty
   HTTPResponse --->holds response
     

